abstract: Commerce Department reports gross domestic product rose at 3.9 percent annual rate in second quarter, up from previously reported rate of 3.7 percent.
lead_paragraph: A report from the Commerce Department showed gross domestic product rising at an annual rate of 3.9 percent in the second quarter, buoyed by consumer spending.

headline.main: G.D.P. Growth in 2nd Quarter Is Revised Up to 3.9%
headline.print_headline: G.D.P. Growth in 2nd Quarter Is Revised Up to 3.9%
